result.execSummary:
The defendant Darrell A Killebrew was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. On one or more other charges, Darrell A Killebrew was found not guilty. These charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Darrell A Killebrew is presumed innocent of the not guilty charges.

  • Darrell A Killebrew was found guilty of Battery [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).
  • Darrell A Killebrew was found guilty of Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).
  • Darrell A Killebrew was found guilty of Child Abuse-Recklessly Cause Harm, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.03(3)(b).
  • Darrell A Killebrew was found guilty of Battery [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).
  • Darrell A Killebrew was found guilty of Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).
  • Darrell A Killebrew was found guilty of Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Defendant Darrell A Killebrew in court with attorney Patrick Thomas Earle.  Defendant Darrell A Killebrew in custody.  Molly M Schmidt appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Sentencing proceeded. PSI reviewed. Statements by parties and defendant. 

AS TO COUNT 2
The court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM term in the Wisconsin State Prison of 5 MONTHS, consecutive to Counts 4, 5, 6, 7 and all other cases AND concurrent to Count 3, with credit for 97 DAYS time served.  The term of INITIAL CONFINEMENT is 5 MONTHS.

AS TO COUNT 3
The court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM term in the Wisconsin State Prison of 3 MONTHS, consecutive to Counts 4, 5, 6, 7 and all other cases AND concurrent to Count 2, with credit for 97 DAYS time served.  The term of INITIAL CONFINEMENT is 3 MONTHS.

AS TO COUNT 4 AMENDED
The court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM term in the Wisconsin State Prison of 2 YEARS, consecutive to all counts and cases, the term of INITIAL CONFINEMENT is 1 YEAR, the term of EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 1 YEAR. 

AS TO COUNT 5
The court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM term in the Wisconsin State Prison of 7 MONTHS, consecutive to all counts and cases. The term of INITIAL CONFINEMENT is 7 MONTHS.

AS TO COUNT 6
The court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM term in the Wisconsin State Prison of 3 MONTHS, consecutive to all counts and cases. The term of INITIAL CONFINEMENT is 3 MONTHS.

AS TO COUNT 7
The court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM term in the Wisconsin State Prison of 4 MONTHS, consecutive to all counts and cases. The term of INITIAL CONFINEMENT is 4 MONTHS.

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION
-Batterers Intervention program.
-Mental health evaluation, take all prescribed medications.
-AODA assessment, comply with recommended treatment.
-Absolute sobriety.
-Treatment and/or counseling as determined by agent.
-No contact with victim Angela D. or her children M.K., M.K., C.L., and C.L. during the entirety of sentence, which includes Extended Supervision. Agent may modify.
-Obtain/maintain employment.
-No contact with firearms.
- Pay all MANDATORY court costs, fees, and surcharges including: DNA & DV surcharges to be paid from 25% of prison funds, balance paid during Extended Supervision, failure to pay results in a civil judgment. 
-Court waived all NON-Mandatory court costs, fees and surcharges due to inability to pay.
-No new violations rising to the level of probable cause.

*Court finds defendant is NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program OR the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.
*Court advised defendant of right to seek post conviction relief.
*Court advised defendant of penalties for violation of NO CONTACT ORDER.
*Court advised due to DV conviction under federal law the defendant is prohibited from firearm possession.
*Court advised due to felony conviction the defendant is prohibited from firearm possession, and defendant's voting rights are suspended and may not vote until civil rights are restored.

Defendant Darrell A Killebrew in court with attorney Patrick Thomas Earle.  Defendant Darrell A Killebrew in custody.  Molly M Schmidt appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  At the hour of 1:30 PM the jury returned and, by their foreperson, brought in a verdict which was then read.
COUNT 1: NOT GUILTY.
COUNT 2: GUILTY, as charged in the information.
